        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 22 at 5:24PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 524 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles northeast of Kurthwood, or 16 miles south of Natchitoches,
moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kisatchie, Melrose, Flora, Cypress, Bellwood, Bermuda, and Gorum.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
